The paper deals with the formal verification and repair of timed automata, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several computer science sub-disciplines. However, the focus on abstraction, testing, and synthesis of constraints suggests that the paper is more likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) or Software Engineering (cs.SE) categories. The use of formal methods and automata theory also makes the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category a possible fit. Additionally, the paper deals with temporal requirements and constraints, which could place it in the Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) or Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) categories.
